the objective things we can all

00:17:09.920 --> 00:17:10.720 align:middle line:90%
agree on.

00:17:10.720 --> 00:17:14.089 align:middle line:90%


00:17:14.089 --> 00:17:17.060 align:middle line:84%
I now realize as a
mature man much better

00:17:17.060 --> 00:17:20.390 align:middle line:84%
why I first became
interested as a scientist

00:17:20.390 --> 00:17:22.609 align:middle line:90%
to study consciousness.

00:17:22.609 --> 00:17:24.829 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately I
think my reason was

00:17:24.829 --> 00:17:28.640 align:middle line:84%
to rebel against this feeling
of cosmic indifference.

00:17:28.640 --> 00:17:32.360 align:middle line:84%
I felt that consciousness
ultimately could not

00:17:32.360 --> 00:17:36.530 align:middle line:90%
be explained by science.

00:17:36.530 --> 00:17:40.040 align:middle line:84%
I have two conflicting
impulses [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:17:40.040 --> 00:17:41.450 align:middle line:90%


00:17:41.450 --> 00:17:42.320 align:middle line:90%
Very much so.

00:17:42.320 --> 00:17:44.880 align:middle line:84%
So on the one hand, I was
very much a scientist.

00:17:44.880 --> 00:17:45.680 align:middle line:90%
I love science.

00:17:45.680 --> 00:17:47.840 align:middle line:84%
I love looking and
finding conformation

00:17:47.840 --> 00:17:49.220 align:middle line:90%
of order in the natural--

00:17:49.220 --> 00:17:50.322 align:middle line:90%
in the natural universe.

00:17:50.322 --> 00:17:52.280 align:middle line:84%
That's why I'm a scientist
ultimately because I

00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:54.470 align:middle line:84%
do believe that by
rational process,

00:17:54.470 --> 00:17:56.960 align:middle line:84%
we can understand what this
universe is made out of

00:17:56.960 --> 00:17:59.390 align:middle line:84%
and what we made out
of and why we're here.

00:17:59.390 --> 00:18:02.540 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand, I grew
up as a devout believer,

00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:05.538 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to reconcile those
obviously conflicting things

00:18:05.538 --> 00:18:06.830 align:middle line:90%
and I wanted to reconcile them.

00:18:06.830 --> 00:18:10.760 align:middle line:84%
So on the one hand, I thought,
well, consciousness science

00:18:10.760 --> 00:18:13.395 align:middle line:84%
is going to not be able
to explain that finally,

00:18:13.395 --> 00:18:15.020 align:middle line:84%
and then finally I
have a justification

00:18:15.020 --> 00:18:16.670 align:middle line:90%
for why I believe in a soul.

00:18:16.670 --> 00:18:18.113 align:middle line:84%
But then as I did
it more and more

00:18:18.113 --> 00:18:20.030 align:middle line:84%
and thought about it
more and more, I said no.

00:18:20.030 --> 00:18:21.530 align:middle line:90%
This is-- I don't need a soul.

00:18:21.530 --> 00:18:26.250 align:middle line:84%
I don't need the classical
traditional religious Cartesian

00:18:26.250 --> 00:18:27.050 align:middle line:90%
soul.

00:18:27.050 --> 00:18:30.410 align:middle line:84%
I think you can explain
the strange aspect

00:18:30.410 --> 00:18:33.380 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness,
the subjectivity,

00:18:33.380 --> 00:18:35.930 align:middle line:90%
using physical natural laws.

00:18:35.930 --> 00:18:38.420 align:middle line:84%
You have to extend what
we know about the universe

00:18:38.420 --> 00:18:39.540 align:middle line:90%
a little bit.

00:18:39.540 --> 00:18:41.720 align:middle line:84%
But you can explain
consciousness

00:18:41.720 --> 00:18:44.690 align:middle line:84%
without removing this wonderful
aspect of consciousness

00:18:44.690 --> 00:18:46.430 align:middle line:90%
that it is a feeling.

00:18:46.430 --> 00:18:50.692 align:middle line:84%
It cannot just be reduced
to my neurons in my brain.

00:18:50.692 --> 00:18:53.668 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:53.668 --> 00:19:24.420 align:middle line:90%


00:19:24.420 --> 00:19:30.010 align:middle line:84%
>> There are many possibly
infinite ways of approaching

00:19:30.010 --> 00:19:34.750 align:middle line:84%
consciousness just like in
the story with the blind men

00:19:34.750 --> 00:19:37.420 align:middle line:84%
and the elephant where everyone
had a different perspective

00:19:37.420 --> 00:19:39.160 align:middle line:90%
of what these elephant might be.

00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:47.120 align:middle line:90%


00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:49.850 align:middle line:84%
We have learned over
the last few decades

00:19:49.850 --> 00:19:53.720 align:middle line:84%
that under the ground, a
forest like these trees

00:19:53.720 --> 00:19:57.800 align:middle line:84%
will be connected and
will be talking right now,

00:19:57.800 --> 00:20:00.215 align:middle line:84%
probably whispering about
what I'm talking about.

00:20:00.215 --> 00:20:13.160 align:middle line:90%


00:20:13.160 --> 00:20:16.520 align:middle line:84%
The field of bioacoustics
is just at its infancy

00:20:16.520 --> 00:20:19.040 align:middle line:84%
and we still know
very little, but we

00:20:19.040 --> 00:20:25.400 align:middle line:84%
know the trees and plants are
not only able to detect sounds

00:20:25.400 --> 00:20:28.625 align:middle line:84%
from their environment but would
also produce their own sounds.

00:20:28.625 --> 00:20:34.180 align:middle line:90%


00:20:34.180 --> 00:20:36.220 align:middle line:84%
The incredible
amount of data that

00:20:36.220 --> 00:20:40.150 align:middle line:84%
is emerging in the
field of plant behavior

00:20:40.150 --> 00:20:43.720 align:middle line:84%
and communication is
obviously pointing

00:20:43.720 --> 00:20:48.220 align:middle line:84%
more uncomfortable questions
of whether plants are actually

00:20:48.220 --> 00:20:52.450 align:middle line:84%
sentient, intelligent,
conscious.

00:20:52.450 --> 00:20:58.000 align:middle line:84%
